Internodes vary considerably in length, and so do the hydrothecae, as well as the proportion of the internodes occupied by the hydrothecae. In some colonies (FC07 L 167 ), the hydrothecae extend along 75–86 % of the internode, whereas in others having smaller hydrothecae, only 60–68 % of the internode length is occupied (NEREIDA0610 RD 74 , see
Table 5
). The ratio hydrothecal length/width is also quite varied (between 1.15–1.74 ), with some hydrothecae almost as long as wide, while others are more than 1.5 times longer than wide.
